The '''Elathan''' were a social group<ref name="POTJ">''[[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]''</ref> that shared its name with the [[Elatha system/Legends|Elatha system]], located in the [[Stensen sector/Legends|Stensen sector]] of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]].<ref name="TEAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> They had their first contact with the [[The galaxy/Legends|wider galaxy]] between the [[Standard year/Legends|years]]<ref name="POTJ" /> [[400 BBY/Legends|400]]<ref name="FF">{{FactFile|95|CHU 1-2|''Chu'unthor''}}</ref>&ndash;[[230 BBY/Legends|230 BBY]],<ref name="FF-11">{{FactFile|11|YOD 1-6|Yoda}}</ref> when they were visited by the ''[[Chu'unthor]]'', a vast [[Jedi training/Legends|training]] [[Starship/Legends|ship]] operated by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]. This first contact encounter garnered significant [[Media/Legends|media]] attention across the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]].<ref name="POTJ" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Elathan were created for the ''[[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]'', a [[roleplaying game]] sourcebook published by [[Wizards of the Coast]] in [[2002]].<ref name="POTJ" />

